      "prompt": "Create a 3:4 vertical Xiaohongshu cover image for a friend-recommendation note about the brand “Holly Shit 开心拉屎”. Use the provided reference images as visual references: preserve the recognizable Holly Shit IP / mascot attitude, playful sticker or cup product elements, quirky rebellious brand vibe, and the existing color/graphic language, but do not invent any third-party logos, certifications, UI screenshots, prices, or fake endorsements. Scene: a realistic but stylized office restroom break / desk-corner setup—an overworked young office worker has stepped away from work, with a Holly Shit sticker-covered tumbler or sticker sheet as the main foreground subject occupying about 60–75% of the frame; nearby are harmless lifestyle props like a phone face-down, crumpled to-do note, tissue pack, and a small “pause” sticky note, making the benefit instantly clear: this is a funny anti-anxiety object that gives permission to pause and breathe, not vulgar shock humor. Composition: product/IP centered slightly lower, large and clear, safe margins on all sides; background softly suggests office tiles or a washroom mirror plus desk items, but keep it clean and non-gross. Color palette: warm off-white, mint green, bright yellow, black accents, a little rebellious red; lighting is soft flash / daylight mix, high clarity, playful editorial product photography with cute weird graphic overlays. Add cover text in Chinese only, with two hierarchy levels: large bold main title at top-left or top-center “厕所哲学救我” and smaller subtitle below “3句反焦虑贴纸”; use chunky rounded sans-serif Chinese typography, high contrast, sticker-like outline, no more than these two text blocks. Overall mood: funny, confident, anti-anxiety, slightly rebellious, clean and tasteful, clearly showing the Holly Shit product/IP as a concrete lifestyle solution.",
